* I changed the **release validation** from `refs/heads/sit` to `release/* | hotfix/*`, matching the updated branch strategy. Your current Logger release still checks only `refs/heads/sit`. 
* I set SIT to **no manual approval**, matching the newer release pattern. Your current Logger SIT release still has a business approval stage. 
* I used `UAT_VARIABLE_GROUP` / `PROD_VARIABLE_GROUP` as placeholders. Replace them if your real names differ.
* I used `BUILD - SERVICE - Alterna Logger` as the pipeline definition name. Replace it if your actual Azure DevOps pipeline definition still has a different display name.

The current release pipeline should be replaced by the one above from `targetEnvironment` onward. The original one you pasted is the SIT-only version. 
